An airbag contains 100.0 g of  \( NaN_{3}(s) \)  and 200.0 g of  \( KNO_{3}(s) \) . Calculate the theoretical volume, measured at room temperature and pressure, of the gas produced when the bag is inflated. 

(Formula masses:  \( NaN_{3} = 65.0 \) ,  \( KNO_{3} = 101.1 \) ;
 molar volume of gas at room temperature and pressure = 24 dm\( ^{3} \) )
